**Overall Meaning:**

Sandalwood, born from the love of Krishna and the cowherds, is a destroyer of sin. By its grace, it always gives the fruit of the four goals of life. Even giving just a sesame seed of this sandalwood brings the fruit equal to a mountain of gold. 
